    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    placeListInColumnTwo={true}
    items={[
      {
        title: 'The Glory of God',
        description:
          'The primary focus of Amnion’s ministry is to glorify God. Board members, staff and volunteers endeavor to model Christ in all aspect of their lives.',
        icon: 'tabler:wand',
      },
      {
        title: 'The Word of God',
        description:
          'The Bible is God’s inerrant Word and teaches that salvation is attained by faith alone, in Christ alone. God’s Word is sufficient for teaching, reproof, correction and for training in righteousness. God’s Word teaches that man is created in God’s image and likeness and for His glory; therefore, Amnion’s mission is to uphold the sanctity of human life.',
        icon: 'tabler:settings',
      },
      {
        title: 'The Hope of God',
        description:
          'Amnion will assist anyone facing an unplanned pregnancy, seeking post-abortion healing, and considering sexual purity issues. All counsel is given within a Biblical perspective, which is consistent with God’s design for holy living.',
        icon: 'tabler:presentation',
      },
    ]}
  >
    <Fragment slot='content'>
      <h3 class='heading text-4xl'>Mission and Vision</h3>
      <p class='paragraph mb-5'>
        Amnion’s <strong>mission</strong> is to share the gospel of Jesus Christ and to protect and advocate for the sanctity
        of all human life, born and unborn, through the provision of abortion alternative services that empower mothers to
        choose life.
      </p>
      <p class='paragraph'>
        The <strong>vision</strong> of Amnion is to stop abortion by educating all people on the true value of a human life,
        by using God’s word to show them the love of Christ, and by providing care and support to women and their families.
      </p>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot='contentTwo'>
      <h3 class='heading text-2xl'>We value:</h3>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    isReversed={true}
    image={{
